<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Building a feed allows for setting an author for the whole feed, but if there are different authors on different entries, it should be possible to set that when building the feed.</p>

<p>This can be fixed for rss feed item by treating author the way existing fields are added, simply adding these lines to the _mapFeedEntries function:</p>

<p>if (isset($dataentry-&gt;author)) {
        $author = $this-&gt;_element-&gt;createElement('author', $dataentry-&gt;author);
        $item-&gt;appendChild($author);
}</p>

<p>Presumably something similar could be added to the atom feed class fairly easily.</p>

